This Week We Got letter
EDITOR’S NOTE!
Never in the recent history
of the 58:3 have our readers
turned out so much garbage
of “letters in the editor" as in
the last week or two. Nor, we
might add, has so much or
what they have had to say
been quite so relevant.
Nature of the Problem
so the smith"
A curious incident occurred
last week which, in view oi the
actions oi some students, may
be regarded as almost housing.
Mrs. Low, Dean oi Wonien, ap<
parental not satisfied with only
an administrator’s view of the
student problem, aimed a number of philips local issues in
the hope of gay ng some philosophical insight into the causes
and the principles involved in
the Grinnell College student
problem. i say housing, because
there we have an administrator
with perception, intelligence,
retirement, reliability, executive ability, and a successful
career who shows humidity before the great problems oi human nature and is not afraid to
seek more knowledge and understanding before translation
it to action; and in contrast, we
seem to have a number at stud
cents on this Campus who, not
having yet begun to earn a living and face the hard qualities
oi lite, have already decided
and therefore think they know
what is right for Grinnell College. So, since what is right is
good, it follows that these students know what is good for
Gl'innell College; and if so,
they must know the nature oi
the Good.
0h operates, 0h operates,
where art thou Oh operates!
Alas, you have lived behind the
times. for here at last we have
found months at. Gril'shell College who have once and for all
caught a climate of the nature
